      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Quest’ultima formula ci mostra che, il vettore densità di flusso di probabilità in un determinato punto, è proporzionale alla densità di probabilità in questo punto e al gradiente della fase <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr8" draw:name="Object46" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.1665in" svg:height="0.2083in"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mi>ϕ</mi>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ϕ} {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>VkNMTVRGAQAxAAAAAAAAAAEAGwAAAAkAAAAAAAAAAAABAAAAAQAAAAEAAAABAAAAAaQAAAAL
       AQAADwAAAJYAAQACAAAACQCLAAEAAgAAAP//gQABABAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAKMAAAAKAQAAiwAB
       AAIAAAAAGJUAAQAEAAAAAAAAAJYAAQACAAAACQCLAAEAAgAAAB8AigABAEgAAAAFAEIAAAAQ
       AExpYmVyYXRpb24gU2VyaWYAAAAAAADwAAAAAAAAAAAABQAAAAAAAgD/AwAAAAAAAAABAP8D
       AAAAAAAAAAAAAACIAAEAAgAAAAEAhwABAAUAAAD/////AIYAAQAEAAAAAAAAAHIAAgAXAAAA
       BwAAANcAAAABAD98AAAAAAABAAEA1QOMAAEAAAAAAIwAAQAAAAAAjAABAAAAAAA=
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame><text:s/>della distribuzione di ampiezze di probabilità.</text:p>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2">Formula di diffusione di Rutherford.</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Consideriamo una particella <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> che incide contro una lamina d’oro, e supponiamo di voler determinare la distribuzione di probabilità <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr8" draw:name="Object47" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.4165in" svg:height="0.2665in"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mrow>
           <mi>p</mi>
           <mrow>
            <mo fence="true" form="prefix" stretchy="true">(</mo>
            <mrow>
             <mi>ϑ</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mo fence="true" form="postfix" stretchy="true">)</mo>
           </mrow>
          </mrow>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{p left (ϑ right )} {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>VkNMTVRGAQAxAAAAAAAAAAEAGwAAAAkAAAAAAAAAAAABAAAAAQAAAAEAAAABAAAAAegBAAAo
       AQAAJAAAAJYAAQACAAAACQCLAAEAAgAAAP//gQABABAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAOcBAAAnAQAAiwAB
       AAIAAAAAGJUAAQAEAAAAAAAAAJYAAQACAAAACQCLAAEAAgAAAB8AigABAEgAAAAFAEIAAAAQ
       AExpYmVyYXRpb24gU2VyaWYAAAAAAADwAAAAAAAAAAAABQAAAAAAAgD/AwAAAAAAAAABAP8D
       AAAAAAAAAAAAAACIAAEAAgAAAAEAhwABAAUAAAD/////AIYAAQAEAAAAAAAAAHIAAgAXAAAA
       GwAAAOYAAAABAHB4AAAAAAABAAEAcACMAAEAAAAAAIsAAQACAAAAHwCKAAEAQgAAAAUAPAAA
       AAoAT3BlblN5bWJvbAAAdwAAAPUAAAD//wAAAAAFAAAAAAAAAP8DAAAAAAAAAAEA/wMAAAAA
       AKgAAAAAAIgAAQACAAAAAQCHAAEABQAAAP////8AhgABAAQAAAAAAAAAcgACABoAAACvAAAA
       4QAAAAEAAAAoADkAAAAAAAEAAQAoAIwAAQAAAAAAiwABAAIAAAAfAIoAAQBIAAAABQBCAAAA
       EABMaWJlcmF0aW9uIFNlcmlmAAAAAAAA8AAAAAAAAAAAAAUAAAAAAAIA/wMAAAAAAAAAAQD/
       AwAAAAAAAAAAAAAAiAABAAIAAAABAIcAAQAFAAAA/////wCGAAEABAAAAAAAAAByAAIAFwAA
       APoAAADmAAAAAQA/dgAAAAAAAQABANEDjAABAAAAAACLAAEAAgAAAB8AigABAEIAAAAFADwA
       AAAKAE9wZW5TeW1ib2wAAHcAAAD1AAAA//8AAAAABQAAAAAAAAD/AwAAAAAAAAABAP8DAAAA
       AACoAAAAAACIAAEAAgAAAAEAhwABAAUAAAD/////AIYAAQAEAAAAAAAAAHIAAgAaAAAAlgEA
       AOEAAAABAAAAKQA5AAAAAAABAAEAKQCMAAEAAAAAAIwAAQAAAAAAjAABAAAAAAA=
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame><text:s/>che la particella venga deflessa sotto un angolo <text:span text:style-name="T7"></text:span>.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Prima di tutto osserviamo che non ci potranno essere fenomeni di diffrazione, perché la lunghezza d’onda associata ad una particella <text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> è molto minore della distanza interatomica del reticolo cristallino dell’oro, infatti:</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard"><text:tab/><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr8" draw:name="Object48" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="1.7665in" svg:height="0.5252in"><draw:object>
