       /wMAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIgAAQACAAAAAQCHAAEABQAAAP////8AhgABAAQAAAAAAAAAcgACABcA
       AACnAAAAHgEAAAEAMlAAAAAAAAEAAQAyAIwAAQAAAAAAjAABAAAAAACMAAEAAAAAAA==
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame>. Si procede iterando questa operazione fino a raggiungere una approssimazione soddisfacente.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">In realtà noi eseguiamo solo un passo e come funzione iniziale scegliamo <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr8" draw:name="Object76" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="1.2083in" svg:height="0.2752in"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mrow>
           <msub>
            <mi>ψ</mi>
            <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
             <mn>0</mn>
            </mstyle>
           </msub>
           <mrow>
            <mrow>
             <mo fence="true" form="prefix" stretchy="true">(</mo>
             <mrow>
              <mrow>
               <mi>x</mi>
               <mi>,</mi>
