    </draw:custom-shape><draw:custom-shape text:anchor-type="char" draw:z-index="15" draw:name="Text Box 73" draw:style-name="gr16" draw:text-style-name="P5" svg:width="0.8004in" svg:height="0.5004in" svg:x="5.0189in" svg:y="2.7472in">
     <text:p text:style-name="Frame_20_contents">Fig. 17<text:tab/><text:tab/><text:tab/></text:p>
     <draw:enhanced-geometry draw:mirror-horizontal="false" draw:mirror-vertical="false" draw:glue-points="?f0 0 0 ?f1 ?f0 ?f2 ?f3 ?f1" draw:text-areas="0 0 ?f3 ?f2" svg:viewBox="0 0 0 0" draw:type="ooxml-rect" draw:enhanced-path="M 0 0 L ?f3 0 ?f3 ?f2 0 ?f2 Z N">
      <draw:equation draw:name="f0" draw:formula="logwidth/2"/>
      <draw:equation draw:name="f1" draw:formula="logheight/2"/>
      <draw:equation draw:name="f2" draw:formula="logheight"/>
      <draw:equation draw:name="f3" draw:formula="logwidth"/>
     </draw:enhanced-geometry>
    </draw:custom-shape><draw:custom-shape text:anchor-type="char" draw:z-index="14" draw:name="Text Box 72" draw:style-name="gr16" draw:text-style-name="P5" svg:width="0.8004in" svg:height="0.5004in" svg:x="5.0189in" svg:y="0.7472in">
     <text:p text:style-name="Frame_20_contents">Fig. 16</text:p>
     <draw:enhanced-geometry draw:mirror-horizontal="false" draw:mirror-vertical="false" draw:glue-points="?f0 0 0 ?f1 ?f0 ?f2 ?f3 ?f1" draw:text-areas="0 0 ?f3 ?f2" svg:viewBox="0 0 0 0" draw:type="ooxml-rect" draw:enhanced-path="M 0 0 L ?f3 0 ?f3 ?f2 0 ?f2 Z N">
      <draw:equation draw:name="f0" draw:formula="logwidth/2"/>
      <draw:equation draw:name="f1" draw:formula="logheight/2"/>
      <draw:equation draw:name="f2" draw:formula="logheight"/>
      <draw:equation draw:name="f3" draw:formula="logwidth"/>
     </draw:enhanced-geometry>
    </draw:custom-shape>Nella realtà fisica non avremo un onda piana infinitamente estesa, ma, come mostra la figura 17, avremo un fascio stretto, molto simile ad un onda piana, ma con una dimensione trasversale finita.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">In queste condizioni solo l’onda sferica potrà arrivare al detector, quindi è solo l’onda sferica che dobbiamo considerare per calcolare il flusso di probabilità.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Ora passiamo al calcolo del flusso mediante la formula <draw:frame text:anchor-type="as-char" draw:z-index="73" draw:style-name="gr15" draw:text-style-name="P15" svg:width="1.9169in" svg:height="0.5004in">
