    </draw:frame><draw:custom-shape text:anchor-type="char" draw:z-index="7" draw:name="Text Box 89" draw:style-name="gr18" draw:text-style-name="P5" svg:width="0.9004in" svg:height="0.6004in" svg:x="5.6189in" svg:y="0.4646in">
     <text:p text:style-name="Frame_20_contents">Fig. 20</text:p>
     <draw:enhanced-geometry draw:mirror-horizontal="false" draw:mirror-vertical="false" draw:glue-points="?f0 0 0 ?f1 ?f0 ?f2 ?f3 ?f1" draw:text-areas="0 0 ?f3 ?f2" svg:viewBox="0 0 0 0" draw:type="ooxml-rect" draw:enhanced-path="M 0 0 L ?f3 0 ?f3 ?f2 0 ?f2 Z N">
      <draw:equation draw:name="f0" draw:formula="logwidth/2"/>
      <draw:equation draw:name="f1" draw:formula="logheight/2"/>
      <draw:equation draw:name="f2" draw:formula="logheight"/>
      <draw:equation draw:name="f3" draw:formula="logwidth"/>
     </draw:enhanced-geometry>
    </draw:custom-shape>Per poter applicare questa formula ci resta da determinare il flusso totale incidente <text:span text:style-name="T6">F</text:span>. Per determinare questa grandezza dobbiamo calcolare l’integrale della distribuzione ottenuta sperimentalmente. L’integrale deve essere calcolato considerando che la curva in realtà rappresenta una superficie, che si ottiene facendo ruotare la curva attorno all’asse delle ordinate; quindi non abbiamo un integrale semplice, ma un integrale doppio. Tuttavia per ottenere una stima grossolana noi faremo il calcolo basandoci sull’approssimazione mostrata in figura 20, cioè approssimeremo la superficie con un cilindro, con un raggio di base di 10<text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span> ed un’altezza pari all’altezza massima della superficie, 27 particelle al secondo nell’angolo solido <text:span text:style-name="T6">d</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T1"></text:span>.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard"><draw:custom-shape text:anchor-type="char" draw:z-index="6" draw:name="Text Box 94" draw:style-name="gr17" draw:text-style-name="P5" svg:width="0.5004in" svg:height="0.4004in" svg:x="5.1811in" svg:y="0.0075in">
     <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_5" text:outline-level="5">S</text:h>
     <draw:enhanced-geometry draw:mirror-horizontal="false" draw:mirror-vertical="false" draw:glue-points="?f0 0 0 ?f1 ?f0 ?f2 ?f3 ?f1" draw:text-areas="0 0 ?f3 ?f2" svg:viewBox="0 0 0 0" draw:type="ooxml-rect" draw:enhanced-path="M 0 0 L ?f3 0 ?f3 ?f2 0 ?f2 Z N">
      <draw:equation draw:name="f0" draw:formula="logwidth/2"/>
      <draw:equation draw:name="f1" draw:formula="logheight/2"/>
      <draw:equation draw:name="f2" draw:formula="logheight"/>
      <draw:equation draw:name="f3" draw:formula="logwidth"/>
     </draw:enhanced-geometry>
    </draw:custom-shape>Quindi per il flusso totale abbiamo:</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard"><draw:custom-shape text:anchor-type="char" draw:z-index="5" draw:name="Text Box 93" draw:style-name="gr17" draw:text-style-name="P5" svg:width="0.5004in" svg:height="0.4004in" svg:x="5.2646in" svg:y="0.6091in">
